HGIS de las Indias

Hosted at Harvard Datavase

Description taken from original site: 
  "Spatial and tabular datasets as well as scripts created within the project HGIS de las Indias, a spatio-temporal infrastructure for Bourbon Spanish America. Includes civil and church administrative entities at various levels, settlement types, missionary towns, ports, wharfs, demographic data, data on postal routes, centers of fiscal and other administration, silver registries, printing presses, data on mining mita, and indigenous groups."
  
  

Files of interest:

* Demographic data, 1701-1808 

** Citation: Stangl, Werner, 2019, "Demographic data, 1701-1808", https://doi.org/10.7910/DVN/QABIBG, Harvard Dataverse, V2

  
